name: Warung Nyoman Mujair
address: M9RV+9WG, Batudinding, Kintamani, Bangli Regency, Bali 80652, Indonesia
review 1:
I think we shocked the whole crowd when we walked in. There was like 10 locals gawking at us with faces that said, white people? Are they lost?  After testing the waters and realizing nobody spoke a word of English I gestured my hand to my mouth saying "food." Still seeing their dumbfounded looks, I looked up how to say "how much" and pointed at food laying around.

So the lady started cooking, meanwhile, one of the guys must have run to grab the only guy in town that spoke English.  He and I started tearing thru the kitchen to find out what I wanted, and eventually he started slapping everything on my plate. It wasn't all wonderful, but the fish was the best fish I've had in Indonesia, the portions were big, and the meal was excellent.

During the meal, the guy thought us some words in Balinese and Indonesian and also introduced us to his dog named White.

It caused quite the stir in the room, everyone seemed to be watching us. They made such a fuss about me leaving a 14k tip, I had to leave it on the table cuz they refused to take it. When we went to leave about 12 people individually thanked us for coming.

Total bill for two: 36k rupiah ($2.50)
Experience: priceless.
